Vaccinium angustifolium

   [10700.jpg]
   Authority Aiton
   Family Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Ericales:Ericaceae
   Synonyms Vaccinium brittonii Porter ex C. Bicknell, Vaccinium lamarckii
   Camp, Vaccinium pensylvanicum var. nigrum A.W. Wood
   Common names low-bush blueberry, late sweet blueberry, low sweet
   blueberry, sweet hurts, mirtilho de folhas estreitas, uva do monte de
   folhas estreitas, upland lowbush blueberry
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 10700

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A 15-60 cm tall woody shrub with bluish berries. USES
   The berries are eaten fresh or canned. They can also be used in herbal
   medicines. GROWING PERIOD Perennial shrub, with a minimum growing
   period per year of 100 days. COMMON NAMES Lowbush blueberry, Sweet
   blueberry, Low sweet blueberry, Late sweet bush, Late sweet blueberry.
   FURTHER INF It is widely distributed in woodlands and sunny places
   along the northeastern coast on United States and in northern Europe.
   Seems to thrive more readily after being cut or burned.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 241 [USE, PH, TEXT, DRA]
   Dube P 1982 pp 17
   Duke J 1975 pp 30 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Hartmann T 1981 pp 592-593 [PH, DRA, DEP, LIG, KTMP]

